{%- comment -%}
  Recommendations content, fetched asynchronously by
  snippets/product-recommendations.liquid via routes.product_recommendations_url
  (Shopify's native recommendation engine — no custom "you might also like"
  logic). Kept as its own tiny section rather than inline in main-product.liquid
  so it can be fetched by section id and dropped in without blocking the
  initial product-page render (spec's LCP/performance requirements: the PDP's
  own image + buy box are what matter for first paint, not related products
  below the fold).

  `product` doesn't need deriving here: Shopify's recommendations endpoint
  (routes.product_recommendations_url) injects it into this section's scope
  itself from the `product_id` query param the fetch URL supplies.
{%- endcomment -%}
{% recommendations product: product, limit: 4, intent: 'related' %}
  {%- if recommendations.performed and recommendations.products_count > 0 -%}
    <div class="grid grid-cols-4">
      {%- for recommended_product in recommendations.products -%}
        {% render 'product-card', product: recommended_product %}
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}
{% endrecommendations %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Related products",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
